{
  "text": "It is less clear whether there is also an association between anticoagulant activity at the time of the ICH and hematoma size. We did not find an association between NOAC level-as determined by drug-specific tests-and hematoma size at baseline. The observed association between higher aPTT levels and smaller hematoma volumes is most likely a small-number effect, but requires replication in a larger cohort. Similarly, a baseline INR below 3.0 is not associated with the baseline hematoma volume in VKA-related ICH [CITATION_1] . Attributing hematoma size to intensity of anticoagulation by VKA and NOAC alone might thus be oversimplified, and other factors such as blood pressure should be considered in future studies.",
